            <div class="policy-header">
                <h1>Cancellation Policy</h1>
                <p class="lead">We understand that plans can change. Our flexible cancellation policies are designed to protect both travelers and hosts while giving you peace of mind.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="policy-overview">
                <div class="overview-content">
                    <h2>Why Choose SnapTrip's Cancellation Policy</h2>
                    <p>At SnapTrip, we believe in fair and transparent cancellation terms that balance flexibility for travelers with reliability for hosts. Every booking includes a clear cancellation policy chosen by the host, ensuring you know exactly what to expect.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="overview-features">
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i>
                        <h4>Flexible Options</h4>
                        <p>Choose from multiple cancellation policies when booking, or stick with the host's default policy.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
                        <h4>Quick Refunds</h4>
                        <p>Most refunds are processed within 3-5 business days, with funds appearing in 5-10 days.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-card">
                        <i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i>
                        <h4>Fair Protection</h4>
                        <p>Our policies protect both guests and hosts, building trust in our travel community.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="policy-types">
                <h2>Cancellation Policy Types</h2>
                <p>Each listing displays its cancellation policy clearly. You can choose a different policy during booking if available. Here's what each type means:</p>

                <div class="policy-grid">
                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <div class="policy-header">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Flexible</h3>
                            <span class="badge badge-success">Most Popular</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="policy-details">
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>Full refund</strong> for cancellations made 30+ days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>50% refund</strong> for cancellations made 15-29 days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>No refund</strong> for cancellations made 14 days or less before check-in
                            </div>
                            <p class="policy-description">Perfect for travelers who want maximum flexibility. Ideal for uncertain plans or first-time bookings.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <div class="policy-header">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Moderate</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="policy-details">
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>Full refund</strong> for cancellations made 60+ days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>50% refund</strong> for cancellations made 30-59 days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>No refund</strong> for cancellations made 29 days or less before check-in
                            </div>
                            <p class="policy-description">A balanced option for most travelers. Offers good protection while maintaining host reliability.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <div class="policy-header">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Firm</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="policy-details">
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>Full refund</strong> for cancellations made 30+ days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>No refund</strong> for cancellations made 29 days or less before check-in
                            </div>
                            <p class="policy-description">Best for fixed travel plans and long-term bookings. Provides certainty for hosts.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="policy-card">
                        <div class="policy-header">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-ban"></i> Non-refundable</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="policy-details">
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>No refunds</strong> for any cancellations
                            </div>
                            <div class="refund-rule">
                                <strong>Free changes</strong> up to 7 days before check-in
                            </div>
                            <p class="policy-description">Lowest rates available. Ideal for travelers with confirmed plans who want the best value.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="special-circumstances">
                <h2>Special Circumstances & Exceptions</h2>
                <p>We understand that unexpected events can occur. Here are situations where we may offer flexibility beyond standard policies:</p>

